did.head: DESCRIPTIVE SUMMARY
did.physdesc: Pamphlets, brochures, other miscellaneous printed materials.
did.repository: Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library
did.abstract: Pamphlets relating to city planning and affiliated issues collected by John Nolen in the course of his career.

scopecontent.head: COLLECTION DESCRIPTION
scopecontent.p: Pamphlets relating to city planning and affiliated issues collected by John Nolen in the course of his career.

prefercite.head: Cite As:
prefercite.p: John Nolen pamphlet collection. #6337. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.

relatedmaterial.head: RELATED MATERIALS
relatedmaterial.p: A larger collection of work related to John Nolen can be found in the John Nolen papers, #2903

arrangement.head: COLLECTION ARRANGEMENT
arrangement.p: The collection has been kept in the order Nolen originally provided, cataloged by number. All un-numbered items have been placed at the end of the collection. We have attempted to provide brief, topical descriptions of the materials within a certain numbered category. Nolen also kept an alphabetical card catalog of his materials. An item can be looked up by subject, author, title, etc., and the corresponding number where the item can be found is provided. This card catalog is available for use, and is listed as box 24.
